            "4.1 Minimax completeness": "8/10 — Implements a standard recursive minimax with explicit max/min layers, depth decrement, and terminal/leaf evaluation. Top-level `find_best_turn` selects the argmax and queues a full turn. Minor concerns: correctness depends on external helpers (`enumerate_complete_turns`, apply/undo, `SimBoard`) and the policy has fallback/turn-replay logic that could bypass minimax in some states (mid-jump/end-turn handling).",
            "4.2 Alpha-Beta correctness": "8/10 — Alpha/beta are initialized to ±inf, updated correctly at each node (alpha on max, beta on min), and prunes on `beta <= alpha`. Propagation is by return value and uses apply/undo per child. Potential boundary issues: `turns` is an iterator-like result; if it’s single-pass and reused, ordering/pruning behavior could be impacted, and `current_player` is passed separately from `is_maximizing` (assumes strict alternation 0↔3) which must match game turn rules.",
            "4.3 Heuristic function quality": "9/10 — Multi-factor heuristic with strong signals: terminal win/loss, summed min hex-distance-to-target for both players, bonuses for own pieces in target, penalties for opponent pieces in target. This is well-aligned with Chinese Checkers progress. Minor gaps: doesn’t model mobility/jump potential, blocking/congestion explicitly, or differentiate piece importance, but it is clearly more than a simple distance-only heuristic and logically consistent.",
